		<tr>
			<td><br><img src=/shared_files/techspeakers_photos/Captian_Sean.jpg align=left valign="top">&nbsp;Sean Captain is editor of Popular Science magazine’s What’s New section. Each month, What’s New identifies and explains the greatest technological breakthroughs that appear in all consumer product categories, including electronics, automobiles, sporting goods and home appliances. Having gotten his start in technology as a reviews editor at PC World magazine, Captain then became a freelance writer and editor for several years. His work has appeared in publications and Web sites including The New York Times, Wired, Real Simple, Yahoo!, Laptop, Popular Science, and PC World.<br><br>
A graduate of Georgetown University and a Fulbright Scholar, Captain also worked as an environmental policy analyst and a nonprofit fundraiser.     
